[[div class="jotting" style="border: solid 0.3rem rgb(var(--general-border-color));"]]

[[span class="titled"]]SURREALISTIC CURTAILMENT PRINCIPLES:[[/span]] MEDIATOR's empty containment cell is to be swept twice a day. Its prurient magazines are to be incinerated in [[[scp-6643 | Area-21]]]'s automatic smut disposal unit. In the event that MEDIATOR fully digitizes, personnel are encouraged to kiss their sorry derrières goodbye. Project COUNTERMEDIATION is presently undergoing its final stages.

Before continuing onward, readers must consume, digest, and internalize each section of the description below -- //in sequence// -- or I swear to god I will turn this car around.

----

[[tabview]]
[[tab I]]

[[span class="titled"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] MEDIATOR is an eigen-brand taffy puller designed for the enholement and maintenance of [[[scp-1549 | Class-B "Information Superhighway" Wormholes]]] connecting certain private servers and higher planes, as part of ongoing efforts to cover WAN's bus fare. Shortly following its initial activation, all major GoI-004 servers and webrings worldwide received large bundles of cognitohazardous data; less than 25 hours later, the first known gatherings of GoI-004E were observed to take place.

Anomalous activity associated with GoI-004E includes:

* Proliferation of “chain email curses.”
* Creation of viable spacecraft using spare parts, loose bricks, stray dogs, etc.
* Analog-to-digital haruspicy.
* Dissolution of regional semiospheres.
* Star chart estrangement.

[[/tab]]
[[tab II]]

[[span class="titled"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] MEDIATOR is a parasite primarily composed of fused human fingers. It is 2.5 meters long, smells gently of lilac, and is constantly producing an ontohazardous wireless signal. In the event that this signal bumps into a synthetic intelligence in the hallway, the latter will immediately become a real boy. Host servers are typically rendered inoperable by resultant organic growths. All known real boys have been excised and provided the latest obscene periodicals.

Surrounding matter has been transfigured into noetic swiss cheese, suspending the decomposition process and increasing computing speed by a significantly arbitrary percentage. Department director credentials have been trashed.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Not to be confused with Cpt. Director D. Credentials, who lives in Site-⌘'s omnidirectional dormitories and not the trash.[[/span]]

As HOST BETA cannot be relocated [[span class="blur"]]from Site-41[[/span]] without risking significant structural harm, a [[[scp-7579 | Faraday-Exclusion Field]]] has been built [[span class="blur"]]surrounding sublevel 30.[[/span]]

[[/tab]]
[[tab III]]

[[span class="titled"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] MEDIATOR is a continuous cosmogtological process responsible for the slow-motion car crash of noöspheric[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]][[span class="titled"]]NOÖSPHERE:[[/span]] The sum of all human thought.[[/span]] and cyberspheric[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]][[span class="titled"]]CYBERSPHERE:[[/span]] The sum of all electronically-stored data.[[/span]] territories, otherwise known as the Neosphere, otherwise known as Nx-9923, otherwise known as the MEDIUM. It is presently believed to be responsible for every slow-loading webpage you've never seen, the [[[scp-5470 | Y2K bug]]], and the decimation of all dedicated "computer rooms" in the continental United States.

Should MEDIATOR be allowed to continue unabated, HOST BETA will eventually obtain enough imaginary mass to collapse into a supermassive Class-B Wormhole and slurp up the solar system like spaghettios on rice.

[[/tab]]
[[tab IV]]

[[span class="titled"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] MEDIATOR was a completely ordinary box of matches. In the event that a match is lit, it will burn and produce smoke. And you know how smoke works, don't you? You should understand smoke better than anyone. 

It'll do what it does best: rise. It'll rise over data centers and churches. Over clouds and high-altitude weather balloons. It'll rise high enough to tickle the sky, then higher still. Once it's drifted beyond the sight of even our most powerful radio telescopes and gamma binoculars, the smoke may just touch something. And it may taste something. And it may bring something back.

[[/tab]]
[[tab V]]

